<item>
            <title>[SOLR-74] Cross-site scripting vulnerabilities</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-74</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There are a number of cross-site scripting vulnerabilities in the Solr admin JSP pages, wherever data is being re-displayed as typed by the user.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example, in analysis.jsp:  &amp;lt;textarea class=&quot;std&quot; rows=&quot;1&quot; cols=&quot;70&quot; name=&quot;qval&quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;%= qval %&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/textarea&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These need to be modified to HTML escape the values rather than directly outputting the exact values. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The other affected JSP pages: action.jsp and get-file.jsp&lt;/p&gt;</description>
